<paragraph blockId="4.[264,1325,284,1884]" pageId="4" pageNumber="51">
Remarks. The new species is quite similar to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bickel et Wei" authorityYear="1996" box="[841,1070,1653,1678]" class="Insecta" family="Dolichopodidae" genus="Chrysosoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="51" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cyaneculiscutum">
<emphasis box="[841,1070,1653,1678]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="51">C. cyaneculiscutum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the color of antennae, coxae and legs, but can be easily separated from the latter by the following characters: palpus blackish, 2 strong posterior dc and 3 anterior hairs, It 
<subScript attach="left" box="[962,970,1749,1763]" fontSize="6" pageId="4" pageNumber="51">1</subScript>
somewhat flattened with very short dense ventral pubescence on basal 4/5; in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bickel et Wei" authorityYear="1996" box="[842,1074,1776,1801]" class="Insecta" family="Dolichopodidae" genus="Chrysosoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="51" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cyaneculiscutum">
<emphasis box="[842,1074,1776,1801]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="51">C. cyaneculiscutum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, palpus yellowish, 2 strong posterior dc and 4 anterior hairs, It 
<subScript attach="left" box="[756,764,1832,1846]" fontSize="6" pageId="4" pageNumber="51">1</subScript>
somewhat flattened with very short dense ventral pubescence on basal 1/3.
</paragraph>
